ğŸ¯ Synergia Event Booking API â€“ Assignment 2
ğŸ“˜ Overview

This project is a Node.js + Express.js REST API developed as part of Assignment 2 for managing event bookings for the Synergia Technical Event.
The application connects to MongoDB for persistent data storage and implements CRUD operations for both events and bookings.

ğŸš€ Features

âœ… Connects Node.js API to MongoDB
âœ… Create, Read, Update, and Delete (CRUD) for Events and Bookings
âœ… Query bookings by ID or Email
âœ… Delete booking by Email
âœ… Fetch event details by ID or Title
âœ… Well-structured API responses with success/error messages

ğŸ› ï¸ Technologies Used

Node.js

Express.js

MongoDB Atlas

Postman (for API testing)

âš™ï¸ Installation & Setup
1. Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/synergia-event-booking-api.git
cd synergia-event-booking-api

2. Install Dependencies
npm install

3. Configure MongoDB

Create a .env file (or directly in code) and add your MongoDB URI:

MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster0.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority
PORT=9000

4. Run the Server
node index.js


Server will start at:

http://localhost:9000

ğŸ“¡ API Endpoints
ğŸ§¾ Event Routes
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/api/events	Add a new event
GET	/api/events	Fetch all events
GET	/api/events/:id	Fetch event by ID
DELETE	/api/events/:title	Delete event by title
ğŸŸï¸ Booking Routes
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/api/bookings	Add new booking
GET	/api/bookings	Get all bookings
GET	/api/bookings/:id	Get booking by ID
PUT	/api/bookings	Update booking by email
DELETE	/api/bookings	Delete booking by email
ğŸ§  Example Request Body
Add Event
{
  "title": "Tech Innovators Summit",
  "date": "2025-11-10",
  "location": "Sahyadri College",
  "description": "A national-level technical event"
}

Add Booking
{
  "name": "Deepthi",
  "email": "deepthi@example.com",
  "eventTitle": "Tech Innovators Summit"
}

Delete Booking by Email
{
  "email": "deepthi@example.com"
}

ğŸ§ª Testing Using Postman

Open Postman and set your API base URL: http://localhost:9000

Test endpoints one by one (use raw JSON in body)

Check responses for success or error messages

